column5: Spool up your new spinning gear and save your money up. Here is a lake that has NEVER seen a lure!!! Imagine being the first person tocast for fish here!!! http://www.jpl.nasa.gov/news/news.cfm?release=2007-026
That's wild, it makes you wonder what else is up there.  I get the first cast.
I would think that your Ice auger better have a REALLY long shaft   vance
You don't have to go to Saturn for that. There's tons of lakes in Northern Ontario that have the same status.
Actually was just about to say the same thing. I've fished many tiny lakes in the far north that have very likely never seen another angler before or since
I'm sorry, but fishing in a sea of liquid methane isn't my idea of a fun fishing trip.
Fishin in Methane would be fun, until the first guy goes to light a smoke! HH
Doesn't methane only exist on earth from decay of living matter?
Thats an OFNCers dream if I ever seen one. The fish would probably hit anything
Methane is found all over the place, Rick, not just here at home.
imagine the size of the northern's up there!!
